HEADWORD: Cabazite
<hw>Cab"a*zite</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧b"⟦adot⟧*z⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>chabazi`os</grk> one of twenty species of
stones mentioned in the poem <grk>Peri` li`qwn</grk>, ascribed to
Orpheus.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral occurring in glassy
rhombohedral crystals, varying in color from white to yellow or red. It
is essentially a hydrous silicate of alumina and lime. Called also
<altname>chabasie</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

